    <body>Converts the cursor to Polyline mode, which lets you create a straight or angled line with an arrow at the end (which you can change or remove by using the Polyline section in the Object Properties window pane). After you select this button, you can click anywhere in the frame to identify the starting point for the line. When you move the cursor, a straight line segment is drawn. If you click the left mouse button, it signifies the end of that line segment and the start of another line segment. When you move the cursor, another straight line segment is drawn. You can identify the end of the line by double-clicking.</body>
</html>